@{
    ViewBag.Title = ViewBag.SiteName + "'s Conditions";
}

<h2>@ViewBag.SiteName's Conditions</h2>

<p>
    If you would like to use @ViewBag.SiteName, you must be OK with the following:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        Other people will see the captions you submit.  If you do not submit them anonymously, and you 
        unwisely use your real name, people will be able to identify you.
    </li>
    <li>
        @ViewBag.SiteName can and will remove any of your captions at your request, but has no power to 
        remove them from search engines such as <a href="http://www.google.com/">Google</a> and archivers 
        such as <a href="http://www.archive.org">The Wayback Machine</a>, who will most assuredly
        pick your captions up.
    </li>
    <li>
        By submitting a caption to @ViewBag.SiteName, you retain the copyright but agree to license that caption for use under the
        <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0)</a>
